{"word":"H5413 - נָתַךְ - nâthak - naw-thak' - Drop","slug":"H5413","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָתַךְ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâthak"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-thak'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Drop"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05EA;&#x05DA; - na&#x0302;thak</b> - <i>naw-thak'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>flow</i> forth (literally or figuratively); by implication to <i>liquefy: - </i>drop, gather (together), melt, pour (forth, out)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2046\">H2046</a>"}]}